t-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#477C1D;margin-bottom:4px;display:block;\">info</span>\n                        <h2 style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:20px;font-weight:800;color:#ECF0E9;margin:0;line-height:1.2;\">Stack Trust, Don&#x27;t Scatter It</h2>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n                <p style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:16px;line-height:1.65;color:#CAD0C6;margin:0;overflow-wrap:break-word;word-break:break-word;\">Each additional proof point compounds credibility. But mixing proof types (data + testimonial + visual) is 40% more effective than repeating the same type.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>",
